        "label": "Human Intelligence Alignment",
        "type": "markdown",
        "content": "**BLURB**: Human social order is an achievement. What does that mean? How do social scientists understand the achievement of human intelligence alignment?\n[EDIT SLIDES](https://slides.com/djjr/hmia2025-problem-of-social-order/edit)<iframe src=\"https://slides.com/djjr/hmia2025-problem-of-social-order/embed?style=light&byline=hidden&share=hidden\" width=\"576\" height=\"420\" title=\"HMIA 2025 The Problem of Social Order\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>\n# The Problem of Social Order\nSTATUS (20250806: sacred texts done (might need to edit minilecture comments). Are the handouts ready?) PostClass is (1) reflection of sacred texts and game results (2) apply altruistic punishment to org, exp, AI context (3) discussion board \\- ask an LLM about using sacred text\n\nGOAL: In this class session we want to establish that alignment is a fundamental challenge any time more than one human intelligence is on the scene.\n\nPerhaps another more general way to put it is that human level intelligence makes the world unsafe for other human level intelligences?\n\nARC: Raw materials here can include \"how aligned are you?\" survey results; sacred texts and alignment; Hechter & Horne on social order; Fehr\\&Gintis on prosocial behavior.\n\nAgenda\n\n* 15 Review sacred text exercise from PreClassWork.  \n* 10 Vocabulary  \n* 30 Fehr & Gintis Game  \n  * [Tally Sheet 1](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1WNYlPcez5mvskT_Ou9xy6pIopjwvZ941/edit?usp=sharing&ouid=108740423027992536308&rtpof=true&sd=true)  \n  * [Tally Sheet 2](https://docs.google.com/document/d/11MD_CsEGXxkteXwaAppbL3ZffRh6UzSZ/edit?usp=sharing&ouid=108740423027992536308&rtpof=true&sd=true)\n\n## Concrete Problems of Social Order (Human Alignment)\n\nIf we use as a working definition of human intelligence alignment something like \"humans are safe to be around or among\" or \"individual human behaviors contribute to broader human flourishing\" or just that humans are beneficial for humans then misalignment can come in many forms.\n\nA social order accident …\nCooperation\nCooperation Never Happens: Collective Action Problems\nCooperation Breaks Down: Free Riding\nNorm Enforcement\nCoordination Problems: Language, Shared Meaning, Information Flow\nIncentive Design\nInterpretability and Justification\nOrganizational Drift\nPower Asymmetry\nMalicious use"
