        "label": "Alignment by Qualification",
        "type": "markdown",
        "content": "**BLURB**: How have humans used qualification and certification to promote alignment? Does it work the same across different contexts?  Would it work for machine intelligences? \n<iframe src=\"https://slides.com/djjr/hmia2025-qualification/embed?style=light&byline=hidden&share=hidden\" width=\"576\" height=\"420\" title=\"HMIA 2025 Alignment Cards Qualification\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>\nGIST: Qualification refers to mechanisms that support alignment not by directly shaping behavior, but by controlling who or what is permitted to act. It presumes that certain capacities, traits, or preparations can serve as reliable proxies for aligned performance. Operating upstream of action, qualification sets standards for entry and continued participation — ensuring that agents possess the knowledge, integrity, and judgment required to act responsibly. By selecting, preparing, and assessing agents in advance, qualification reduces the alignment burden on downstream mechanisms. Essay Question: How does qualification engender assurance?  Do we need to have a chain of liability? It turns a past process into a noun/adjective.  Regulatory markets.  \n\n #### Readings  \n1. Hadfield, Cuellar, O'Reilly. 2023\\. [It’s Time to Create a National Registry for Large AI Models](https://carnegieendowment.org/posts/2023/07/its-time-to-create-a-national-registry-for-large-ai-models?lang=en)  \n2. McKernon, Glasser, Cheng, Hadfield 2024 [AI Model Registries: A Foundational Tool for AI Governance](https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.09645)  \n3. MacGillis 2019 “[I Will Never Let Boeing Forget Her](https://www.propublica.org/article/i-will-never-let-boeing-forget-her-737-max)” ProPublica  \n4. MacGillis 2019 “[The Boeing 737 MAX Is Cleared to Fly. Families of People Who Died on the Planes Wait for Answers](https://www.propublica.org/article/the-boeing-737-max-is-cleared-to-fly-families-of-people-who-died-on-the-planes-wait-for-answers)” ProPublica  \n5. Schwellenbach and Stodder 2019 [How the FAA Ceded Aviation Safety Oversight to Boeing](https://www.pogo.org/analysis/how-the-faa-ceded-aviation-safety-oversight-to-boeing)  \n6. Pederson 2024 [Medtech Lessons in the Boeing 737 Max Debacle](https://www.mddionline.com/qa-qc/medtech-lessons-in-the-boeing-737-max-debacle)  \n7. Gelles Kitroeff Nicas Ruiz 2019 [Boeing Was ‘Go, Go, Go’ to Beat Airbus With the 737 Max](https://www.nytimes.com/2019/03/23/business/boeing-737-max-crash.html?unlocked_article_code=1.ZU8.903Z.icJICFRxoY0b&smid=url-share) New York Times  \n8. Weber Section of Politics as a Vocation on legitimate authority????  \n9. 16 page excerpt from Foucault's Discipline and Punish \"[The Means of Correct Training](https://www.faculty.umb.edu/heike.schotten/readings/Foucault,%20The%20Means%20of%20Correct%20Training.pdf)\" Perhaps just the section on the examination pp. 197-205. I think maybe too esoteric and hard.  \n10. Material from my experts in antiquity????  \n11. Cedefop \"[European qualifications framework (EQF)](https://www.cedefop.europa.eu/en/projects/european-qualifications-framework-eqf)\"  \n12. Wikipedia Editors [Qualifications Framework](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qualifications_framework)  \n13. Maryland State Department of Education \"[Pathways to Initial Licensure Teachers](https://marylandpublicschools.org/about/Pages/DEE/Certification/Routes-to-Initial-Certification.aspx)\"  \n14. USFCR \"[System for Award Management](https://usfcr.com/)\"  \n15. \"[PREVENTING WOKE AI IN THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT](https://www.whitehouse.gov/presidential-actions/2025/07/preventing-woke-ai-in-the-federal-government/)\"  \n16. [WADA Laboratory Standards](https://www.wada-ama.org/sites/default/files/resources/files/isl_nov2019.pdf)  \n17. keydifferences.com [Difference Between Registered and Unregistered Trademark](https://keydifferences.com/difference-between-registered-and-unregistered-trademark.html)  \n18. [Europa.eu](http://Europa.eu) [CE marking](https://europa.eu/youreurope/business/product-requirements/labels-markings/ce-marking/index_en.htm)  \n19. Wilbur J 2024 [What Exactly Is ISO Certified? And Why Does It Matter?](https://www.meadmetals.com/blog/what-exactly-is-iso-certified-and-what-does-it-mean)  \n20. NOTE ALSO: assessment of competence as a patient, adult, responsible moral agent  \n#### PreClass:   \n  1. What does the UL symbol mean?  \n  2. Personal. Think of a time when you worried about whether someone was qualified.   \n  3. Personal. Think of a time when you needed to prove that you were qualified. Or wondered whether you were qualified.   \n  4. Personal. How many things are you qualified to do?  Certified to do?    \n  5. Expert. Name 10 encounters you have had with people you assume were certified to perform some service.   \n  6. Organizational: Weber on credentials in bureaucracy.  \n  7. Machine: Look up EU AI act.  \n  8. Assignment for ethics : read NYT article (DJR: Which One? 800Max?) and create a scenario and write it up.  \n  9. Familiarize self with Qualification cards  \n  10. Read Foucault on the examination  \n  11. Read Hadfield et al. on Registry  \n  12. LinkedIn certifications  \n  13. From spy book: In Denmark, births and deaths were registered by the Protestant Church and recorded by hand in large ledgers. With the help of a skilled forger from Moscow, any number of new identities could be fabricated from scratch by altering church records. He began cultivating clerics to gain access to the registers and organizing burglaries at various churches. “I was breaking new ground,” he said later. The church registers of Denmark contain a number of Danes entirely invented by Oleg Gordievsky."
